This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Zyere Q Grandberry

records.addlTxt: CORRECTION: Judge Konkol presided over Branch 13 on August 31st, 2022

Defendant Zyere Q Grandberry not in court.  Attorney Sam Obscherning in court for Zyere Q Grandberry.  Prosecuting attorney Nate Kristian McClure in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case set for a calendar call.  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued forthwith. COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE BENCH WARRANT. Court FORFEITS BAIL SUBJECT TO APPROPRIATE NOTICE.

Attorney Sam Obscherning in court.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney appeared by video means.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until the next court date.
Court ordered case adjourned for calendar call in Branch 37.
  All parties are advised effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to a Branch of RESERVE JUDGES.  Calendar call scheduled for August 31, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Attorney Michael Fuentes for Sam Obscherning in court, defendant Zyere Q Grandberry not in court, in custody.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney appeared by video means. Defense counsel has not received discovery and offer. Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 37.   This hearing may be streamed live on Dacast at the Court's discretion:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/3c595ccd-39e3-09d4-8db1-82162d766d4f  Status conference scheduled for July 21, 2022 at 09:00 am.

No driving without a valid license.
Court ordered him not to drive in any vehicle unless he knows the owner of the vehicle and they have a valid drivers license.
DEFENDANT WAS ORDERED BY THE COURT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON (5/18/2022). IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with J.G.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Zyere Q Grandberry in court.  Matthew Richard Westphal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 37 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 05/16/2022@1pm
